This article is about an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on June 25, 2013. The order establishes the President's Advisory Council on Financial Capability for Young Americans, with the aim of promoting financial capability among young Americans and encouraging financial education at an early stage in schools, families, communities, and the workplace. The council will consist of members appointed by the President, including individuals with experience in improving financial capability for young people. The council's functions include collecting information and views on financial capability, advising the President and the Secretary of the Treasury on implementing financial capability policies, and periodically reporting on progress. The Department of the Treasury will provide funding and administrative support for the council. The council will terminate two years after the date of the order, unless extended by the President. The order also states that it should be implemented consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.